></div><div class="labelHeader">Description:</div><div class="normalText"><p>The Senior-Level Intelligence Collection Support Analyst will be responsible for providing Intelligence Integration Support to the National Intelligence Management Council (NIMC) within the Office of the Director of National Intelligence, Deputy Director for Intelligence Integration (DNI/DDII).</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>Responsibilities include:</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>+ Providing collection subject matter expertise to support the assigned AOR in strategy-related activities .</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>+ Helping to assess progress against key intelligence gaps identified in the strategies.</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>+ Assisting with analyzing strategic collection initiatives and requirements to ensure their alignment with national level intelligence priorities, objectives and organizational missions and goals.</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>+ Working with internal elements and other departments and agencies engaged in collection activities to coordinate joint actions and ensure alignment of programs, procedures, and guidelines.</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>+ Assisting in helping to align and integrate the IC collection enterprise&#39;s total collection capabilities.</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>+ Assisting. with fostering and cultivating strategic alliances and professional networks with interagency partners and other community elements to ensure adequate resource availability and priority attention on a variety of IC-related strategies.</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>+ Base-lining and analyzing JC collection capabilities and postures.</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>**Minimum Education and Experience**</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>Bachelor&#39;s Degree and 5 years work experience or equivalent experience</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>**Required Skills and Education**</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>+ 15+ years of demonstrated experience with addressing intelligence collection-related issues, and in-depth expertise on domestic, defense, United States national, and foreign partners&#39; intelligence collection organizations, programs, and capabilities.</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>+ Significant demonstrated experience with successfully leading senior-level interagency teams or bodies that have achieved decisive results; including the ability to develop .near- and long term strategies, set goals, establish metrics, measure progress, and oversee budgets.</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>+ Significant demonstrated experience interacting with Congressional, intelligence, and policy audiences.</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>+ Significant demonstrated experience conceptualizing and leading complex projects with little supervision and juggling multiple, competing priorities.</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>+ Demonstrated knowledge with the regional or functional area of responsibilities (AOR).</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>**About BAE Systems Intelligence &amp; Security**</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>BAE Systems is a premier global defense and security company with approximately 90,000 employees delivering a full range of products and services for air, land and naval forces, as well as advanced electronics, security, information technology solutions and customer support and services. Information Solutions, based in Reston, Virginia, is among the 10 largest IT providers to the U.S. government, serving most of the federal defense and civilian marketplace. It provides network-centric command, control, computing, and intelligence (C3I) solutions; wideband networking radio systems; information systems for the U.S. intelligence community; geospatial information services; and information technology services. Leveraging its knowledge of signals and data derived from signals, Information Solutions has attained a market-leading position in advanced information technology research, intelligence analysis and production, and geospatial exploitation software. Equal Opportunity Employer/Females/Minorities/Veterans/Disabled/Sexual Orientation/Gender Identity/Gender Expression</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>**EEO Career Site**</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>Equal Opportunity Employer. Minorities . females . veterans . individuals with disabilities . sexual orientation . gender identity . gender expression</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>**Department**</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>0FE000_Geospatial &amp; Security Analysis</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>**Company**</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>GDE_BAE Systems Info Solutions,Inc</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>**Sr. Intelligence Collection Support Analyst (NIMC)**</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>**McLean, Virginia**</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>**16853BR-1651**</p><br /><br /><div style="text-align:left;padding-bottom: 20px;"><a href="/frca-apply/bk087r" id="ApplyBottomLink" target="_blank" class="bigBlueButtonLink" rel="nofollow" onclick="javascript:setTimeout(&quot;window.location.href = &#39;/post-resume?jid=bk087r&#39;;&quot;,1500); return true;">Go to apply&nbsp;<img src="/Images/applyarrow.png" height="21x;" width="16px;" alt="" /></a></div></div></div></div><div style="background-color: #fcfcfc; max-width: 400px;" class="sideBar"><br /><div style="text-align:left;vertical-align:top;padding-left:5px;"><h4 style="padding-bottom:7px;">Similar Skills</h4><p style="padding-bottom:4px;"><a href="/jobs/support-analyst/mclean/virginia/united-states" onclick="ga(&#39;send&#39;, &#39;event&#39;, &#39;Links&#39;, &#39;SimilarSkillsLocationJob&#39;, &#39;0&#39;);">support analyst jobs in McLean, VA</a></p><p style="padding-bottom:4px;"><a href="/jobs/intelligence/mclean/virginia/united-states" onclick="ga(&#39;send&#39;, &#39;event&#39;, &#39;Links&#39;, &#39;SimilarSkillsLocationJob&#39;, &#39;1&#39;);">intelligence jobs in McLean, VA</a></p><p style="padding-bottom:4px;"><a href="/jobs/analyst/mclean/virginia/